eadable as Ronson, matching the product context, and it appears to be the fuel source. The lighter then floats alone against the starry background, returning to a simple side view.\n\nA real product display follows on a plain dark background. On the left stands a tall cylindrical Ronson fuel container with a narrow nozzle at the top; on the right is the Varaflame lighter in side view. A hand enters from the right and grips the lighter, rotating it to show its compact shape and shiny, sculpted surface. Another hand reaches in from the left, takes the Ronson fuel container, and turns it upside down above the lighter. The nozzle is positioned directly over a small opening or valve on the top of the lighter. The hand presses the fuel container down into place, demonstrating a direct filling action with no visible disassembly. The container is then lifted away, leaving the lighter held upright in the hand.\n\nThe hand turns the lighter back into side view. A thumb or finger flips the hinged top open, and a flame appears at the right end. The lid closes, then the lighter is shown again with the flame lit. A second finger approaches from the right and touches a small control near the flame area. As the finger presses or slides this control, the flame becomes much taller, illustrating the adjustable flame feature.\n\nThe scene returns to animation with two oversized Varaflame lighters moving across a sleek, futuristic-looking floor. The background has soft abstract shapes, like a modern display setting. Tiny animated figures ride on the lighters like streamlined vehicles. One lighter is lighter-toned and gleaming; another appears darker and more contrasty, suggesting different finishes. A figure crouches over the front of the lighter as its lid opens and a flame rises. The lighter glides away, and another darker model remains, also opening to produce a tall flame.\n\nThe final images focus on the product name. The word “Varaflame” appears large in graceful script across a softly shaded background. A tiny animated figure riding a lighter passes beneath it. More text appears, forming “Varaflame by Ronson,” with “Ronson” in large capital letters underlined. The commercial ends on this clear brand title: “Varaflame by Ronson.”",
